@pickled_egg: NOT TRUE. TV have resolutions 352x240 for NTSC and 352(384)x288 pixels PAL/SECAM. What confuses people is "line doubling". Higher resolutions came with SVHS, but it was just on side of reproduction source abilities, not TV itself.
